headlines.description: — Paul George scored 22 points, Kawhi Leonard added 19 and the Los Angeles Clippers rallied for their third straight victory, 112-102 over the Chicago Bulls on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers rally in fourth quarter to extend winning streak to 3 with 112-102 victory over Bulls

headlines.description: — Miles Bridges had 24 points and 10 rebounds, Brandon Miller added 23 points and the Charlotte Hornets delivered another blow to the Brooklyn Nets’ sagging playoff hopes with a 110-99 win on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miles Bridges scores 24, Hornets beat Nets 110-99 to snap 6-game losing streak

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic became the first NBA player to record six consecutive 30-point triple-doubles as the Dallas Mavericks pulled away in the second half and beat the Detroit Pistons 142-124 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic is first NBA player to have 6 straight 30-point triple-doubles as Mavericks top Pistons

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 29 points, Jaylen Brown added 27 and the NBA-leading Boston Celtics beat the Phoenix Suns 117-107 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum, Jaylen Brown lead Celtics past Suns 117-107, snapping rare 2-game skid

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Jonathan Kuminga attacked the rim and tried to will the Golden State Warriors back into the game. They just couldn't get enough timely stops.
headlines.shortLinkText: Johnson, Sochan lead Spurs past Warriors team without Curry, 126-113

headlines.description: — Michael Malone needn't have worried about his superstar center and a potential letdown when the Denver Nuggets faced the short-handed Utah Jazz.
headlines.shortLinkText: No letdown: Murray, Jokic, Porter Jr. lead Nuggets to 142-121 rout of short-handed Utah Jazz

events.name: Toronto Raptors at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Deandre Ayton returned from a right hand sprain and had a season-high 30 points and 19 rebounds to help the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Toronto Raptors 128-118 in overtime on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ayton has season-high 30 points and Trail Blazers hold off Raptors 128-118 in OT
